title: SpaceX planning launch of two Falcon Heavy missions in summer and fall
summary: SpaceX plans two Falcon Heavy launches this year for the U.S. Space Force in July and October, and United Launch Alliance has four national security space missions on its 2021 schedule, according to a military spokesperson.

title: Falcon Heavy could launch three U.S. Space Force missions in 2022
summary: USSF-67 is the third U.S. national security launch to be added to the Falcon Heavy’s crowded 2022 manifest.

title: Launch preps underway for first of up to five Falcon Heavy missions this year
summary: SpaceX is set to kick off a busy week of launch preparations at Kennedy Space Center for the first of five planned Falcon Heavy rocket missions this year, targeting a dusk departure no earlier than Thursday evening from Launch Complex 39A on a flight for the U.S. Space Force.

title: U.S. Air Force X-37B spaceplane to launch on a SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket
summary: The seventh mission of the reusable U.S. Air Force X-37B spaceplane is scheduled to launch Dec. 7 on a SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket from Kennedy Space Center, Florida.

title: United States Space Force Prepares to fly OTV-7
summary: The Department of the Air Force Rapid Capabilities Office, in collaboration with the United States Space Force, is slated to launch the seventh mission of the X-37B Orbital Test Vehicle (OTV) via SpaceX’s Falcon Heavy rocket no earlier than Sunday, December 10, 2023.
